			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Product Manager - Mobile Application Platform</p>
<p>
Company Description</p>
<p>
Located in Toronto, Palo Alto, and New York City, Xtreme Labs leads the world in creating the best mobile, tablet and smart TV experiences for the most trusted companies across the globe.<br />
For more information visit http://www.xtremelabs.com.</p>
<p>
Are you passionate about mobile technology and building great platforms?&nbsp; Have you been responsible for defining and building the next-gen application platform?&nbsp; Xtreme Labs is seeking a great product manager who has the vision and drive combined with solid technical background to create game changing approaches to our mobile application platform.&nbsp;&nbsp; You will do customer development, actively gather requirements to shape a successful product.&nbsp; You will work alongside multiple teams including Business Development, Marketing and CEO to help define a compelling product vision and strategy, work directly with world-class engineers to execute it.</p>
<p>
As a Mobile Platform Product Manager, you will be a progressive self-starter who is capable of thinking strategically as well as staying focused on achieving rapid hands-on results.&nbsp;&nbsp; You will manage requirements definition and function as the Product Owner of an agile product team working closely with development and QA to build platform features that are aligned with product strategy and business objectives.</p>
<p>
<br />
Responsibilities include (but not limited to)</p>
<p>
Define, price and launch the next-gen mobile application platform<br />
Analyze relevant product to capture competitive gaps.<br />
Do customer development and validated learning<br />
Work closely with Business Development, Marketing, Graphic Design and Engineering to define and prioritize product features required to execute the product strategy<br />
Function as Product Owner for an agile product team throughout the product lifecycle including: roadmap planning, prioritization, manage backlog and story acceptance</p>
<p>
What we&rsquo;re looking for:</p>
<p>
3-5 years of Mobile Experience<br />
5+ years of experience in development and launching great products<br />
BS/MS in Computer Science or a related technical field, MBA would be a plus.&nbsp;<br />
Ability to understand at a technical level, complex enterprise systems, and how multiple components work together as part of a system<br />
Ability to motivate and rally individuals and teams within the organization<br />
Outstanding communication skills, both written and verbal<br />
Experience interfacing with internal (business development, engineering, marketing) and external constituent (prospective customers, partners)<br />
Must be willing to work hard, be a self-starter and have a can-do attitude<br />
A &ldquo;roll up the sleeves&rdquo; attitude, a self-starting innovative leader who is comfortable working in a fast-paced environment</p>
]]></description>
