<p>
<strong>Description</strong></p>
<p>
Manages a variety of commercial contracts in accordance with company polices and procedures, applicable laws, and customer requirements. Provides on-site advice to Xtreme Lab&rsquo;s business units and project teams on contract management and compliance matters.</p>
<p>
The Contract Manager will manage several engagements at one time.</p>
<p>
<strong>Primary Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Respond to complex inquires regarding contract obligations and revisions<br />
&bull; Draft, evaluate, negotiate and execute: Non-Disclosure Agreements, Sales / Purchasing Agreements, Sub-Contracts, Consulting Agreements, Licensing Agreements, Master Agreements, review of customer proposed terms and conditions, and other contract documentation<br />
&bull; Serve as point of contact for customers on contractual matters and liaise between company employees and customers, ensuring timely review and approval of contracts.<br />
&bull; Act as the primary contact between the business units and Legal, ensuring that all legal and contractual matters are addressed efficiently and promptly<br />
&bull; Provide continual review to ensure that all terms and conditions of contracts are met.<br />
&bull; Prepare and disseminate information to all relevant parties regarding contract status, compliance, and modifications in order to provide contract visibility and awareness.<br />
&bull; Work with risk management team members / Finance to coordinate contractual insurance requirements<br />
&bull; Monitor client satisfaction with our terms and conditions and contracting practices. Recommend changes where appropriate.<br />
&bull; As needed, provide guidance on contract matters to project managers account managers or other employees, including training to new employees in contracting practices and procedures.<br />
&bull; Develop and implement procedures for contract management and administration in compliance with company policies.<br />
&bull; Prioritization of tasks to ensure that critical items (contracts, renewals, meetings) are completed in a timely manner.</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<p>
Education/Experience Requirements</p>
<p>
&bull; Bachelor Degree<br />
&bull; 2+ years of contract management experience<br />
&bull; Formal training in contract law or contract administration is an asset<br />
&bull; Knowledge of the standards and practices of a software technology company is preferred.</p>
<p>
<strong>Skills/Qualifications</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Comprehensive knowledge in contract management.<br />
&bull; Excellent contract drafting and negotiation skills, in particular in the area of software and licensing contracts<br />
&bull; Strong relationship and interpersonal skills to be applied in working with clients across the entire contract life cycle.<br />
&bull; An ability to determine contractual and financial exposure and or risk, and negotiate contracts.<br />
&bull; Strong project and process management skills, with the ability to handle multiple vendors and multiple contract, as well as a wide range of tasks<br />
&bull; Must be able to meet deadlines and work under pressure against competing priorities and timelines<br />
&bull; Must have demonstrated ability to work independently, take initiative, and be attentive to detail</p>
